node.text:
Mayweather isn't just a boxer...he's a businessman. He's built a HUGE name for himself leading to an estimated $450M net worth(other networths have been reported for 2021).

His upfront fee for his fight against Paul was said to be $10M. Overall he reported he'll make between $50M and $100M.

This is the difference between him and many athletes...it takes a great businessman to be able to make big pay days like this.

Watch the ful video here: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=r4fcOyfVoLE&t=77s

Follow us @businessequity

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Business Equity on August 24, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'HOW PETER THIEL LEGALLY AVOID TAXES In 1999, Peter Thiel purchased 1.7 million "founder's shares" of Paypal for $1,700 ($0.001 per share) within his Roth IRA. After Paypal IPO'd, Thiel sold his Paypal shares, and used the proceeds to invest in other startup companies. Today, the value of his account is $5 billion with no additional contributions. Thiel can continue to purchase and sell investments in his Roth IRA without incuring any taxes. When Thiel reaches 59.5 years old, he can withdraw his totl account balance entirely tax-free. BusinessEquity'.

node.text:
FedEx was about to go bankrupt and the founder decided to take the money he had left and went on a gambling trip.

Almost every major company has a different story to success. What works for one person may not work for you...find your own path!

Follow us @businessequity
